intro: Tetracera williamsii, commonly known as the Williams' tetracera, is a flowering plant belonging to the family Euphorbiaceae. It is native to tropical regions of Southeast Asia, including parts of Malaysia and Indonesia. The plant is characterized by its simple, alternate leaves and small, clustered yellowish flowers. It typically grows as an erect shrub or small tree, reaching heights of up to 3 meters. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a rare and ecologically significant species in its native range.
